* Flask
* REST API design
* HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
* JSON request handling
* SQLite integration
* SQL CRUD operations
* Request validation
* Exception handling
* Modular application architecture

---

# 🎯 Looking Ahead

I now understand how Python applications can expose functionality through REST APIs. This lays the foundation for building full-stack web applications, integrating frontend interfaces, and eventually creating AI-powered web services that communicate through APIs.
